From: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
Date: Thu, 16 May 2013 16:38:22 +0200
Subject: scsi_dh_alua: Do not attach to RAID or enclosure devices
Patch-Mainline: submitted to linux-scsi
References: bnc#819979

RAID or enclosure management devices should be ignored when
detecting ALUA capabilites.

Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>

diff --git a/drivers/scsi/device_handler/scsi_dh_alua.c b/drivers/scsi/device_handler/scsi_dh_alua.c
index 1196d7f..3ce4e22 100644
--- a/drivers/scsi/device_handler/scsi_dh_alua.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/device_handler/scsi_dh_alua.c
@@ -327,6 +327,14 @@ static int alua_check_tpgs(struct scsi_device *sdev, struct alua_dh_data *h)
 {
 	int err = SCSI_DH_OK;
 
+	if (sdev->type == TYPE_RAID || sdev->type == TYPE_ENCLOSURE) {
+		h->tpgs = TPGS_MODE_NONE;
+		sdev_printk(KERN_INFO, sdev,
+			    "%s: disable for enclosure devices\n",
+			    ALUA_DH_NAME);
+		return SCSI_DH_DEV_UNSUPP;
+	}
+
 	h->tpgs = scsi_device_tpgs(sdev);
 	switch (h->tpgs) {
 	case TPGS_MODE_EXPLICIT|TPGS_MODE_IMPLICIT:
